-- Copper Gains 0.3% to $8,386.50 Per Ton in London; Shanghai Contract Climbs
-- B y   H e l e n   S u n
-- 2010-12-01T01:07:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-01/copper-gains-0-3-to-8-386-50-per-ton-in-london-shanghai-contract-climbs.html
Copper futures in Shanghai and London
advanced. The metal gained for the third day on the Shanghai
Futures Exchange, rising as much as 1 percent to 63,300 yuan a
metric ton.  Three-month-delivery copper on the London Metal Exchange
increased as much as 0.3 percent to $8,386.50 a ton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helen Sun in Shanghai at 
 hsun30@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
